# Security & RBAC Rules

## Auth Enforcement Order — MANDATORY on every protected handler

```
1. x-vng-admin-key  checked against VNG_ADMIN_API_KEY env var
2. x-vng-operator-id  +  registered role binding in AppState  (operator paths)
3. x-vng-tenant-id  +  x-vng-user-id  (tenant paths)
```

- Return `401` for missing headers
- Return `403` for present-but-invalid credentials
- Mixed surfaces (ingest): check admin/operator first, fall through to tenant
- **Never** add a `skip_auth: bool` or any bypass path

## Tenant Isolation
- All queries on tenant paths must filter by `tenant_id`
- Audit records emitted from tenant operations must carry `x-vng-tenant-id`
- Autonomous records must include `tenant_scope` metadata

## Secret Hygiene
- Never log header values or API key material
- KMS key IDs must come from `env::var("VNG_KMS_*")` — no hardcoded ARNs/URIs
- Never return raw secrets in error responses

## Plugin Security
- Verify signature before loading any plugin manifest
- Reject unsigned manifests with `403`
- Invoke revocation policy hook before trusting any manifest
